		<div class=3D"unnumbered" data-type=3D"exercise" id=3D"fs-idm82243888">
			<div data-type=3D"problem" id=3D"fs-idm82243632">
				<p id=3D"fs-idp88700464">Suppose that on a certain stretch of highway, =
cars pass at an average rate of five cars per minute. Assume that the durat=
ion of time between successive cars follows the exponential distribution.</=
p>
				<ol id=3D"fs-idm57552288" type=3D"a">
					<li>On average, how many seconds elapse between two successive cars?</=
li>
					<li>After a car passes by, how long on average will it take for anothe=
r seven cars to pass by?</li>
					<li>Find the probability that after a car passes by, the next car will=
 pass within the next 20 seconds.</li>
					<li>Find the probability that after a car passes by, the next car will=
 not pass for at least another 15 seconds.</li>
				</ol>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
